4. Ask the user to enter 1, 2 or 3. If they enter a 1, display the message “Thank you”, if they enter a 2, display “Well done”, if they enter a 3, display “Correct”. If
they enter anything else, display “Error message”.
user_inp = input("Enter 1, 2, or 3: ")
if user_inp=="1":
  print("Thank you")
elif user_inp=="2":
  print("Well done")
elif user_inp=="3":
  print("Correct")
 else:
 print("Please enter only 1, 2, or, 3.")
